etymologies: mid 17th century: from French dissyllabique, via Latin from Greek disullabos ‘of two syllables’

definitions: (of a word or metrical foot) consisting of two syllables.
shortDefinitions: (of word or metrical foot) consisting of two syllables

definitions: (of a bird's call) consisting of two distinct sounds, such as the call of the cuckoo.
shortDefinitions: (of bird's characteristic call) consisting of two distinct sounds, such as call of cuckoo
